<item>
            <title>[LU-19068] The quota is not released in time after large file is deleted</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19068</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The quota usage is refreshed in qsd_op_end, which is called when the transaction is stopped.&lt;br/&gt;
If some large file is deleted, the blocks occupied by this file could have not been deleted when&lt;br/&gt;
the transaction is stopped,  then the quota won&apos;t be released in time and can cause other write&lt;br/&gt;
to fail with -EDQUOT.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
